solution: class Solution {
    public int repeatedStringMatch(String a, String b) {
        int al = a.length(), bl = b.length();
        int max = (bl / al) + 2;
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        for (int i = 1; i <= max; i++) {
            sb.append(a);
            if (sb.indexOf(b) != -1) return i;
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O((m + n) * n)
space complexity: O(m + n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Build repeated copies of a until the combined length is at least b's length plus one extra copy. Check each step with indexOf; worst-case repeats are bounded by ceil(|b|/|a|)+2.

